1. cs.IT (Information Theory): The paper deals with channel estimation and achievable rates, which are key topics in information theory. 
2. cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture): The paper discusses a device-to-device (D2D) underlaid massive MIMO system, which is a networking architecture. 
3. cs.SY (Systems and Control): The paper proposes a pilot scheduling and pilot power control algorithm, which can be seen as a control problem. 
4. cs.MM (Multimedia): The paper discusses a system that can potentially support multimedia applications, which falls under the scope of this category. 
5. cs.COM (Computers and Society): This category is less likely, but the paper does touch upon the topic of quality of service (QoS) for cellular users, which can be seen as a societal concern.
